p4
VCASSETTES/CDS&#8216;Njanappana,' the CD contains stanzas from the seminal composition of Poonthanam, a forerunner of the bhakti movement in Kerala. Written in Malayalam, the work dubbed &#8216;the word of wisdom' for its philosophical import is one of the most cherished and popular compositions in the language. Bhavyalakshmi Saji, a researcher in Music at the University of Calicut and a B-High grade artiste of Akashavani, has rendered the composition.Initial salutationThe disc opens with the sounds of the conch followed by the edakka played by Krishnakumar, thus creating a temple-like ambience. In her rich voice, Bhavyalakshmi Saji recites the initial salutation &#8216;Gurunathan thunai cheiga santhatham' and continues it with the oft-quoted &#8216;Innaleyolam yenthen arinjila' in raga Natta.The singer then gives expression to the rest of the stanzas of &#8216;Njanappana' by tying them together as in a garland in ragas Sahana, Malayamarutham, Sanmughapriya, Dhanyasi, Bagesri, Mohanam, Subhapantuvarali, Hamsanandhi, Hamsanaadham, Kedaragowla, Attana, Saveri, Hindolam, Ranjini, Anandabhairavi Sivaranjini and concludes with Madhyamavati. She is accompanied by Rison, Murali, Ramakrishnan and Santhosh on the flute, the veena and the tabla, respectively. Bhavyalakshmi plays the violin herself while Mohandas is in charge of the orchestration, and Anil does the rhythm programming.Recorded at Chetana Sound Studios, Thrissur, &#8216;Njanappana' has been produced by Devadatham Music.
